WEBVTT

00:00:01.879 --> 00:00:03.423
[rain falling]

00:00:03.507 --> 00:00:06.179
[rumbling]

00:00:06.262 --> 00:00:08.935
Huh? Yikes. What's that?

00:00:09.018 --> 00:00:12.943
♪

00:00:13.026 --> 00:00:13.945
Huh.

00:00:14.780 --> 00:00:15.615
[CHIHO]
That claw.

00:00:16.115 --> 00:00:17.451
He's from the Malebranche.

00:00:17.536 --> 00:00:19.038
Why's he here?

00:00:19.706 --> 00:00:21.125
I'd better tell Mister Maou.

00:00:21.209 --> 00:00:22.837
[flashing]

00:00:22.921 --> 00:00:24.675
You all see it, too, right?

00:00:24.758 --> 00:00:25.593
[MALE STUDENT 18A]
Shit, dude.

00:00:27.054 --> 00:00:28.641
[CHIHO]
I can't feel anything.

00:00:29.225 --> 00:00:31.437
My idea link
isn't getting through to him.

00:00:31.522 --> 00:00:32.983
I'll try Miss Suzuno.

00:00:33.066 --> 00:00:35.195
What is it? I just can't tell.

00:00:35.279 --> 00:00:36.532
-Can you?
-Ah!

00:00:36.615 --> 00:00:38.744
My guess is, uh...

00:00:38.828 --> 00:00:41.499
It's some kind of big beast
that escaped from the zoo!

00:00:43.211 --> 00:00:45.465
[CHIHO]
Big old demon, big old demon!

00:00:45.550 --> 00:00:48.054
[sneezes]

00:00:48.764 --> 00:00:49.600
[groans]

00:02:22.952 --> 00:02:24.246
[MAOU]
What's the deal?

00:02:24.330 --> 00:02:26.585
Trust no one,
not even the weatherman.

00:02:27.294 --> 00:02:29.006
-[ACIETH] 'Sup now, Maou?
-Uh?

00:02:29.089 --> 00:02:31.302
Hey! How did the test go?

00:02:31.385 --> 00:02:32.722
My hope is small.

00:02:32.805 --> 00:02:35.268
Yeah, I couldn't really read
about half of the questions.

00:02:35.352 --> 00:02:37.816
Slow your roll with testing
and study a bit more

00:02:37.899 --> 00:02:39.945
so you don't waste
another application fee.

00:02:41.824 --> 00:02:42.784
[MAOU]
Uh?

00:02:43.284 --> 00:02:44.328
[ACIETH sniffs]

00:02:44.411 --> 00:02:47.042
Stop that. I told you not to--

00:02:47.125 --> 00:02:49.506
The hell did I do
to deserve that, you freak?

00:02:49.589 --> 00:02:50.591
Hm...

00:02:51.384 --> 00:02:52.261
Here me out, Dad.

00:02:52.344 --> 00:02:53.973
I think this guy
might be the one.

00:02:54.056 --> 00:02:56.143
-Mm?
-Can I show him now?

00:02:56.227 --> 00:02:57.647
[NORD]
Don't draw any attention.

00:02:59.734 --> 00:03:00.945
[gasps]

00:03:04.118 --> 00:03:06.372
Wait a sec,
your hair is exactly like--

00:03:06.999 --> 00:03:08.459
Knew it! Mm.

00:03:08.544 --> 00:03:10.881
It was your smell
that gave it away for me!

00:03:10.965 --> 00:03:12.885
Am I that ripe?

00:03:12.969 --> 00:03:13.846
Kind of.

00:03:13.929 --> 00:03:16.350
So, you're close
with my big sis, aren't you?

00:03:16.434 --> 00:03:17.645
Wait, who's your "big sis?"

00:03:17.729 --> 00:03:20.400
Come on.
You know Alas Ramus, right?

00:03:20.483 --> 00:03:21.528
Huh?

00:03:21.612 --> 00:03:23.156
Of course, I do!

00:03:23.239 --> 00:03:24.576
She's the older sister?

00:03:24.659 --> 00:03:25.995
Yup! Big sis!

00:03:26.078 --> 00:03:27.624
Okay, once more.

00:03:27.707 --> 00:03:29.878
You're positive
you're not the older one?

00:03:29.961 --> 00:03:32.007
-I mean, looks like it to me.
-I'm not!

00:03:32.090 --> 00:03:34.721
[MAOU] Maybe I'm getting
caught up in the details here,

00:03:34.804 --> 00:03:36.808
but you're like twice her size?

00:03:36.892 --> 00:03:38.520
And I can understand you.

00:03:38.604 --> 00:03:39.814
What can I say?

00:03:39.898 --> 00:03:42.444
I guess I'm just very mature
and elegant for my age!

00:03:42.528 --> 00:03:44.532
-What a flirt!
-Give me a break!

00:03:45.534 --> 00:03:46.578
[MAOU]
I'll cut to the chase.

00:03:46.662 --> 00:03:49.291
You two are from Ente Isla,
aren't you?

00:03:49.375 --> 00:03:50.251
Big boy.

00:03:50.335 --> 00:03:52.924
Tell me your real name,
maybe we're long-lost buds.

00:03:54.343 --> 00:03:55.470
[ACIETH, NORD]
Hm?

00:03:55.554 --> 00:04:00.523
[speaking in foreign language]

00:04:03.987 --> 00:04:05.073
That language.

00:04:05.156 --> 00:04:07.411
Centrient, yeah? Throwback.

00:04:07.494 --> 00:04:09.164
[ACIETH] I don't think
we should worry, Dad.

00:04:09.248 --> 00:04:10.458
Maou's not an angel.

00:04:10.543 --> 00:04:12.170
Even I can tell that much.

00:04:13.799 --> 00:04:16.555
My name is, drumroll,
Acieth Alla!

00:04:16.638 --> 00:04:18.809
Tsubasa's my incognito name!

00:04:19.561 --> 00:04:22.065
Gotcha.
Picked that out yourself?

00:04:22.149 --> 00:04:24.612
[ACIETH] Yup!
Pretty elegant and mature, huh?

00:04:26.323 --> 00:04:31.292
[MAOU speaking
in foreign language]

00:04:32.461 --> 00:04:37.429
[speaking in foreign language]

00:04:38.807 --> 00:04:40.060
I thought I knew everyone

00:04:40.143 --> 00:04:42.105
who had come here
from Ente Isla.

00:04:42.189 --> 00:04:44.068
Looks like you two
just proved me wrong.

00:04:44.819 --> 00:04:46.447
You're also my very first clue.

00:04:47.032 --> 00:04:49.119
So I'm not letting you
out of my sight.

00:04:49.746 --> 00:04:50.623
A clue for?

00:04:50.706 --> 00:04:51.708
[sighs]

00:04:52.292 --> 00:04:54.046
I'm looking for somebody.

00:04:54.129 --> 00:04:55.966
Do you know Emilia Justina?

00:04:56.050 --> 00:04:57.219
[gasps]

00:04:57.302 --> 00:04:59.264
We haven't heard from her
in a few weeks.

00:05:00.391 --> 00:05:02.730
Not a single word
since she left for Ente Isla.

00:05:02.814 --> 00:05:04.233
-Stop there!
-[gasps]

00:05:04.316 --> 00:05:08.491
[speaking in foreign language]

00:05:08.575 --> 00:05:09.451
Cool it, man!

00:05:09.536 --> 00:05:11.748
I just told you
we lost all contact with her!

00:05:11.832 --> 00:05:14.754
[gasping]

00:05:14.838 --> 00:05:16.006
[thuds]

00:05:16.090 --> 00:05:18.302
So, she went home?

00:05:18.386 --> 00:05:20.014
Figured you two were connected.

00:05:20.683 --> 00:05:22.687
But you must be even tighter
than I thought.

00:05:22.770 --> 00:05:25.526
-[cell phone vibrating]
-Ah.

00:05:25.609 --> 00:05:27.404
She seems important to you.

00:05:28.072 --> 00:05:29.032
Let me guess.

00:05:30.160 --> 00:05:32.790
My truthful name
is Nord Justina.

00:05:32.874 --> 00:05:35.796
And yes, your friend Emilia...

00:05:36.590 --> 00:05:37.884
is my daughter.

00:05:38.426 --> 00:05:40.013
[SUZUNO] <i>Pick up the phone,
you fool!</i>

00:05:40.096 --> 00:05:40.931
[MAOU, ACIETH]
Ah!

00:05:41.558 --> 00:05:42.518
Don't yell at me!

00:05:42.602 --> 00:05:44.772
Quickly!
There's no time to spare!

00:05:44.856 --> 00:05:47.277
Uh, jeez, Suz!
You're busting my brain!

00:05:47.360 --> 00:05:50.033
Yes, because you failed
to answer your phone!

00:05:50.116 --> 00:05:52.538
Come back! We need your power!

00:05:52.622 --> 00:05:55.001
Huh? It's gonna have to wait.

00:05:55.669 --> 00:05:57.088
I'm right in the middle
of something here.

00:05:57.172 --> 00:05:59.134
[SUZUNO]
<i>We received an SOS from Chiho!</i>

00:05:59.217 --> 00:06:00.053
Lead with that!

00:06:00.136 --> 00:06:01.932
[SUZUNO]
You see the storm, yes?

00:06:02.015 --> 00:06:03.560
It's centered in Sasazuka.

00:06:03.644 --> 00:06:05.773
Specifically,
good Chiho's school.

00:06:06.650 --> 00:06:08.319
Any clue why?

00:06:08.402 --> 00:06:11.367
[SUZUNO] I don't know whether
it's an angel, demon, or human.

00:06:11.450 --> 00:06:13.580
But someone
is deploying a massive spell.

00:06:13.664 --> 00:06:15.124
One that controls the weather.

00:06:15.668 --> 00:06:18.674
Lucifer and I won't hold out
on our own for very long.

00:06:18.757 --> 00:06:20.594
You need to get back here
immediately!

00:06:20.678 --> 00:06:23.809
[sighs] Why's everything
happening at the same time?

00:06:23.892 --> 00:06:24.727
[sighs]

00:06:24.811 --> 00:06:27.608
Don't really wanna leave
these guys here.

00:06:27.692 --> 00:06:28.986
Maybe I can help, Maou.

00:06:29.069 --> 00:06:30.823
-Uh...
-I heard your friend's voice

00:06:30.906 --> 00:06:32.702
-in my head.
-[gasps]

00:06:32.785 --> 00:06:34.496
So, I guess
you're all caught up then?

00:06:34.580 --> 00:06:36.375
Yeah. Pretty much.

00:06:36.458 --> 00:06:37.878
What comes next?

00:06:37.962 --> 00:06:39.882
And, uh,
know it wouldn't be great

00:06:39.966 --> 00:06:41.636
if you disappeared on us
right now.

00:06:41.720 --> 00:06:43.389
Got it,
and right back at you, kid.

00:06:44.182 --> 00:06:45.686
I need to get home quickly.

00:06:45.769 --> 00:06:47.565
And I want to bring you two.

00:06:47.648 --> 00:06:49.652
But how could I manage that?

00:06:49.736 --> 00:06:51.447
How about we all just fly there?

00:06:51.531 --> 00:06:53.744
Yeah, sure,
on a chariot pulled by unicorns!

00:06:53.827 --> 00:06:56.331
Hush up!
Point me in the right direction!

00:06:56.415 --> 00:06:58.377
-Huh?
-[ACIETH] Let's go!

00:06:58.461 --> 00:07:02.385
[MAOU, NORD yelping]

00:07:02.469 --> 00:07:04.306
[WOMAN 18A]
Are they floating?

00:07:05.726 --> 00:07:06.728
Are you crazy?

00:07:06.811 --> 00:07:08.648
These mofos will exorcise us!

00:07:08.732 --> 00:07:11.153
[MAOU screaming]

00:07:11.236 --> 00:07:12.656
Which way now, Maou?

00:07:12.740 --> 00:07:14.326
I don't know. Crap!

00:07:14.409 --> 00:07:15.913
I'm all turned around.

00:07:15.996 --> 00:07:17.457
It's a weather spell, right?

00:07:17.541 --> 00:07:19.796
Seems to me like
we should follow the weather!

00:07:20.421 --> 00:07:22.008
We gotta hurry over there.

00:07:22.760 --> 00:07:23.678
Don't lose your butts!

00:07:23.762 --> 00:07:25.682
-Now, let's fly!
-Hold on!

00:07:25.766 --> 00:07:27.686
[screams]

00:07:27.770 --> 00:07:28.939
[crashes]

00:07:29.022 --> 00:07:32.947
[roars]

00:07:33.030 --> 00:07:34.449
You think we're gonna be okay?

00:07:34.534 --> 00:07:37.497
-Maybe if we run.
-What the hell is going on?

00:07:37.581 --> 00:07:38.959
[MALE TEACHER 18A]
Stop yelling at me!

00:07:39.042 --> 00:07:40.294
[CHIHO]
If I don't do something quick,

00:07:40.378 --> 00:07:41.881
somebody's gonna get hurt.

00:07:42.758 --> 00:07:44.427
-[door sliding]
-Hey, come back!

00:07:45.096 --> 00:07:46.431
What are you doing?

00:07:46.516 --> 00:07:47.768
[CHIHO] I hope
Mister Maou and the others

00:07:47.852 --> 00:07:49.187
don't get too mad at me.

00:07:50.273 --> 00:07:53.445
[panting]

00:07:55.784 --> 00:07:59.584
<i>♪ The sun is up
It's morning once again</i>

00:08:00.418 --> 00:08:04.092
<i>♪ The day is full of hope, so</i>

00:08:04.176 --> 00:08:06.096
-[rumbles]
-[gasps]

00:08:06.180 --> 00:08:08.685
[LIBICOCCO]
Celestial force-using scum.

00:08:08.768 --> 00:08:11.106
Are you the one
who called me to this entry?

00:08:11.190 --> 00:08:12.358
Thank goodness.

00:08:12.442 --> 00:08:14.112
You can speak my language.

00:08:14.196 --> 00:08:15.281
[LIBICOCCO]
Who are you?

00:08:15.364 --> 00:08:17.118
Why did you beckon me here?

00:08:17.202 --> 00:08:19.164
For a lotta reasons,
Mister Demon.

00:08:19.749 --> 00:08:22.003
Mostly,
to get in the first word.

00:08:22.086 --> 00:08:23.882
'Cause the teachers
and other students

00:08:23.965 --> 00:08:25.844
may do something
that makes you mad.

00:08:25.928 --> 00:08:26.846
[LIBICOCCO]
Ha!

00:08:26.930 --> 00:08:29.852
Big talk for someone
with so little force.

00:08:29.936 --> 00:08:32.357
And for someone
who sounds so small.

00:08:33.275 --> 00:08:34.361
[CHIHO]
Mister?

00:08:34.444 --> 00:08:37.618
Could you use your power
to open this door?

00:08:38.410 --> 00:08:40.540
No biggie for a Malebranche,
right?

00:08:40.624 --> 00:08:43.128
-[LIBICOCCO sighs and grunts]
-[metal breaking]

00:08:43.212 --> 00:08:45.634
-[whimpers]
-[metal breaking]

00:08:45.717 --> 00:08:47.303
-[glass shattering]
-[grunts]

00:08:47.387 --> 00:08:48.472
[crashes]

00:08:48.557 --> 00:08:50.476
-[wind whooshing]
-Uh...

00:08:50.561 --> 00:08:51.395
♪

00:08:51.478 --> 00:08:54.527
[LIBICOCCO] You certainly look
like a human from this country.

00:08:54.610 --> 00:08:56.488
So, you're the one

00:08:56.573 --> 00:08:58.785
that brat Farfa
was talking about.

00:08:58.868 --> 00:09:00.956
You're King Satan's new general.

00:09:01.039 --> 00:09:03.377
The future MgRonald's barista?

00:09:03.460 --> 00:09:05.339
Farfa-- Oh!

00:09:05.423 --> 00:09:07.427
You mean that Fart-fellow guy!

00:09:08.304 --> 00:09:09.139
How nice.

00:09:09.222 --> 00:09:11.811
It sounds like he took care
of all the introductions for me.

00:09:11.894 --> 00:09:13.773
[laughs]

00:09:13.857 --> 00:09:16.403
You are clearly no actor,
small general.

00:09:16.486 --> 00:09:17.990
Your voice is trembling.

00:09:18.617 --> 00:09:19.660
You must know by now

00:09:19.744 --> 00:09:22.165
you can't hide fear
from a demon.

00:09:22.916 --> 00:09:25.463
I am Libicocco,

00:09:25.547 --> 00:09:27.760
one of the leaders
of the Malebranche.

00:09:28.469 --> 00:09:31.141
Not some pee-pants baby
like Farfa.

00:09:32.143 --> 00:09:33.228
I rejoice to hear

00:09:33.312 --> 00:09:35.859
that the Demon King Satan
is alive and well.

00:09:36.569 --> 00:09:39.366
But I refuse
to accept these new "generals"!

00:09:39.449 --> 00:09:41.871
-[wind whooshing]
-[gasps] Ah.

00:09:41.954 --> 00:09:43.875
[rain falling]

00:09:44.459 --> 00:09:45.336
[RIKA]
Mister Ashiya.

00:09:45.419 --> 00:09:46.839
[groans]

00:09:48.425 --> 00:09:50.847
You can't sit in silence
forever, you know.

00:09:51.473 --> 00:09:53.394
Please, ma'am, may I?

00:09:53.477 --> 00:09:55.857
No way, you have to tell me
what's going on.

00:09:55.941 --> 00:09:57.068
Ah, yes, of course,

00:09:57.151 --> 00:10:00.366
I don't doubt you have questions
aplenty about us now.

00:10:00.449 --> 00:10:02.996
[RIKA] I've always thought you
were a pretty mysterious guy.

00:10:03.957 --> 00:10:06.128
I've had questions
since we first met,

00:10:06.211 --> 00:10:07.548
but we haven't gotten
close enough

00:10:07.631 --> 00:10:09.384
for me to ask you
anything personal.

00:10:09.467 --> 00:10:10.637
Yes, I see.

00:10:10.721 --> 00:10:13.601
But now, I think
I deserve some answers.

00:10:13.685 --> 00:10:14.895
Right. What fun.

00:10:15.522 --> 00:10:17.150
So, I'll ask you one more time.

00:10:17.233 --> 00:10:19.905
How the heck did your buddies
just fly out that window?

00:10:20.448 --> 00:10:22.953
They didn't even have fairy dust
or a damn reindeer!

00:10:23.036 --> 00:10:23.913
All right.

00:10:23.997 --> 00:10:25.458
Well, the truth is...

00:10:25.542 --> 00:10:26.586
Tell me.

00:10:26.627 --> 00:10:28.923
...Suzuno and Urushihara,
they...

00:10:29.508 --> 00:10:30.384
Go on.

00:10:30.468 --> 00:10:31.888
...were chosen to participate

00:10:31.971 --> 00:10:35.311
in the trials
of a new energy drink.

00:10:35.394 --> 00:10:37.524
-[RIKA] What?
-And this, you see,

00:10:37.608 --> 00:10:38.693
was a rare side effect.

00:10:38.777 --> 00:10:41.448
That's not what they mean
by "it gives you wings!"

00:10:41.532 --> 00:10:42.450
Like, come on!

00:10:42.534 --> 00:10:45.707
The building across from yours
has to be over ten meters away!

00:10:45.790 --> 00:10:47.251
If they were able to make
that crazy jump

00:10:47.335 --> 00:10:48.630
without a running start,

00:10:48.713 --> 00:10:50.382
they better win Japan the gold!

00:10:50.466 --> 00:10:51.677
[ASHIYA]
We can only hope.

00:10:51.761 --> 00:10:53.515
Look, I know that you know!

00:10:53.598 --> 00:10:56.228
You were way more disapproving
than surprised!

00:10:56.311 --> 00:10:59.234
It so wasn't your first time
seeing something like that!

00:11:00.027 --> 00:11:01.864
I find myself in a dilemma.

00:11:01.948 --> 00:11:04.870
That even if I told the truth,
you wouldn't believe it.

00:11:06.206 --> 00:11:08.252
I just saw
two people fly out the window,

00:11:08.335 --> 00:11:10.005
so I'm pretty down
for believing.

00:11:10.715 --> 00:11:11.842
Of course.

00:11:11.926 --> 00:11:13.095
[rustles]

00:11:13.178 --> 00:11:17.103
You see...
We are not from Japa--

00:11:17.186 --> 00:11:18.355
-[gasps]
-Uh?

00:11:18.438 --> 00:11:21.571
-Ashiya! Let me in!
-[ASHIYA] Ah!

00:11:21.654 --> 00:11:24.952
We're freezing out here.
Come on!

00:11:25.035 --> 00:11:27.081
-[groaning]
-[ASHIYA] Your Majesty!

00:11:27.164 --> 00:11:29.127
Why are you entering
through the window?

00:11:29.210 --> 00:11:30.964
[window sliding]

00:11:31.047 --> 00:11:33.176
[ASHIYA] Who are these strangers
you're letting in our home?

00:11:33.260 --> 00:11:34.387
[NORD grunts]

00:11:34.470 --> 00:11:37.393
Cold, can't think.
I'll explain later.

00:11:37.476 --> 00:11:39.648
Keep an eye on him for me.

00:11:39.732 --> 00:11:41.443
Huh? Mister Maou?

00:11:41.527 --> 00:11:43.990
Oh, Rika, what's up, girl?

00:11:45.200 --> 00:11:47.204
Well, I'm in a bit of a hurry.

00:11:47.288 --> 00:11:48.541
But we'll catch up.

00:11:49.292 --> 00:11:51.379
Watch him. Hawk-level, man.

00:11:51.463 --> 00:11:53.509
Under no circumstances
can we afford

00:11:53.593 --> 00:11:55.346
to let Ponytail
out of our sight.

00:11:55.429 --> 00:11:58.435
I'll do as you wish, Sire,
but I don't understand.

00:11:58.519 --> 00:12:00.022
Come on, Maou! Let's go!

00:12:00.105 --> 00:12:01.232
Yeah, you're right.

00:12:02.068 --> 00:12:03.905
I'm sorry,
we'll talk later, okay?

00:12:03.988 --> 00:12:06.661
Wait, my lord.
That girl, is she--

00:12:06.744 --> 00:12:08.497
It's time to hit the sky!

00:12:08.581 --> 00:12:10.334
Sorry! I'll be back soon--

00:12:10.417 --> 00:12:12.421
[screams]

00:12:12.506 --> 00:12:14.342
[rain falling]

00:12:14.425 --> 00:12:17.014
Sir, may I bother you
for some dry clothing, please?

00:12:17.098 --> 00:12:18.685
After you tell me who you are!

00:12:18.768 --> 00:12:19.603
So, he...

00:12:20.270 --> 00:12:22.274
can fly, too?

00:12:26.659 --> 00:12:28.078
[rain falling]

00:12:32.713 --> 00:12:35.217
-You don't even know this guy?
-Mm.

00:12:37.096 --> 00:12:38.348
[ASHIYA]
Not at all.

00:12:39.935 --> 00:12:42.481
You'll have to forgive
my manners, Miss Suzuki.

00:12:42.566 --> 00:12:44.152
I'm about to be a touch rude.

00:12:44.235 --> 00:12:45.070
Huh?

00:12:45.154 --> 00:12:46.866
[speaking in foreign language]

00:12:46.949 --> 00:12:50.372
[speaking in foreign language]

00:12:50.456 --> 00:12:52.376
Huh? Huh?

00:12:53.045 --> 00:12:57.136
[speaking in foreign language]

00:12:57.721 --> 00:13:01.144
[speaking in foreign language]

00:13:01.227 --> 00:13:06.237
[speaking in foreign language]

00:13:22.896 --> 00:13:26.946
[ASHIYA speaking
in foreign language]

00:13:27.029 --> 00:13:27.864
[speaking in foreign language]

00:13:27.948 --> 00:13:31.872
[ASHIYA speaking
in foreign language]

00:13:31.956 --> 00:13:36.882
[speaking in foreign language]

00:13:36.966 --> 00:13:38.385
"Emilia"?

00:13:38.468 --> 00:13:42.268
You must be--
I can't believe I found you.

00:13:42.351 --> 00:13:43.646
And that I found Maou.

00:13:43.729 --> 00:13:45.440
-Hm?
-[NORD] Your master,

00:13:45.525 --> 00:13:47.696
the man known as Maou
I came here with,

00:13:47.779 --> 00:13:50.743
is the "chosen one"
of which my wife spoke.

00:13:50.827 --> 00:13:52.789
-The chosen one?
-Hello?

00:13:52.873 --> 00:13:54.083
[NORD]
It's something my wife said.

00:13:54.166 --> 00:13:55.002
Wait a sec!

00:13:56.087 --> 00:13:57.381
[NORD]
"When the chosen one is ready

00:13:57.464 --> 00:13:59.887
to expose
the truth of this world,

00:13:59.970 --> 00:14:02.391
'bring the wings'
to our daughter."

00:14:03.184 --> 00:14:05.732
When I first heard
Maou say my daughter's name,

00:14:05.815 --> 00:14:07.401
I knew he was the one.

00:14:07.484 --> 00:14:09.030
That seems like a bold assu--

00:14:09.113 --> 00:14:10.575
-Shut up!
-[gasps]

00:14:10.658 --> 00:14:13.246
I don't know what kind
of Pig Latin bullcrap that was,

00:14:13.330 --> 00:14:15.710
but one of you guys
is gonna have to fill me in!

00:14:15.793 --> 00:14:17.923
[NORD]
You are very scary, miss.

00:14:18.006 --> 00:14:18.966
Watch it, Pops.

00:14:19.050 --> 00:14:21.387
We don't call ladies scary
around here.

00:14:21.471 --> 00:14:23.768
The appropriate term
is "empowered", got it?

00:14:23.851 --> 00:14:24.686
[NORD]
"Pops"?

00:14:24.770 --> 00:14:26.356
[ASHIYA]
I'll tell you everything,

00:14:26.439 --> 00:14:27.358
I promise.

00:14:27.441 --> 00:14:30.364
So please,
take a seat and try to relax.

00:14:30.447 --> 00:14:33.579
Don't think those strong hands
can distract me so easily.

00:14:33.663 --> 00:14:34.706
[ASHIYA]
Huh?

00:14:34.790 --> 00:14:36.794
[RIKA]
What's the deal with this guy?

00:14:36.835 --> 00:14:38.213
This man before you...

00:14:38.296 --> 00:14:39.423
[RIKA]
Yes?

00:14:39.508 --> 00:14:41.177
...claims
to be Miss Yusa's father.

00:14:41.260 --> 00:14:42.096
Got it.

00:14:43.390 --> 00:14:44.225
Huh?

00:14:47.147 --> 00:14:48.943
So, what brings you to Japan?

00:14:49.026 --> 00:14:51.615
Or should I say, to Earth,
Mister Libi-Liberachi?

00:14:52.449 --> 00:14:54.913
Your pronunciation
deeply offends me.

00:14:54.997 --> 00:14:58.378
-[CHIHO] Huh?
-Li-bi-co-cco! Say it.

00:14:58.461 --> 00:15:00.215
Like, Libi-coconut?

00:15:00.298 --> 00:15:02.136
-Try again!
-Uh, sure.

00:15:02.219 --> 00:15:03.556
Just know this.

00:15:03.639 --> 00:15:04.473
If you had butchered

00:15:04.558 --> 00:15:07.062
Draghignazzo's
or Scarmiglione's name

00:15:07.146 --> 00:15:08.314
as you have mine,

00:15:08.398 --> 00:15:11.154
you would be sorely missing
your head right about now.

00:15:11.237 --> 00:15:12.907
Oof. That first one's a toughie.

00:15:12.991 --> 00:15:15.663
Dra-dragon, draggin
deez-what-now?

00:15:15.747 --> 00:15:17.917
Again. Libicocco.

00:15:18.001 --> 00:15:19.253
Libicockroach?

00:15:19.336 --> 00:15:20.715
Libicocco!

00:15:20.798 --> 00:15:22.009
Libicocco!

00:15:22.092 --> 00:15:24.430
Good! You're not so terrible
when you try.

00:15:24.514 --> 00:15:26.142
Uh, thank you.

00:15:26.225 --> 00:15:28.188
Okie-doke, one more shot.

00:15:28.271 --> 00:15:30.651
Why are you here,
Mister Libicocco?

00:15:31.444 --> 00:15:32.655
To rampage.

00:15:32.739 --> 00:15:33.783
Say what?

00:15:33.866 --> 00:15:36.287
[roars]

00:15:36.370 --> 00:15:38.793
-[wind whooshing]
-[gasps]

00:15:38.876 --> 00:15:41.799
[wind howling]

00:15:41.882 --> 00:15:43.552
Please! Stop, Mister!

00:15:43.636 --> 00:15:45.556
[roars]

00:15:45.640 --> 00:15:49.815
[thunder rumbling and crackling]

00:15:49.898 --> 00:15:50.817
This is bad!

00:15:50.900 --> 00:15:52.821
-[thunder crackling]
-[fire blazing]

00:15:52.904 --> 00:15:54.699
[thunder crackling]

00:15:54.783 --> 00:15:57.162
[laughs]

00:15:57.246 --> 00:15:59.709
[gasping]

00:15:59.793 --> 00:16:02.422
[fire blazing]

00:16:02.507 --> 00:16:04.426
No. But why?

00:16:04.511 --> 00:16:06.430
[whooshing]

00:16:06.515 --> 00:16:07.767
Am I losing brain cells,

00:16:07.851 --> 00:16:09.729
or is this storm
getting even gnarlier?

00:16:09.813 --> 00:16:11.692
It is!
Should I pick up the pace?

00:16:11.775 --> 00:16:14.029
I was actually
about to suggest slowing down!

00:16:14.113 --> 00:16:15.448
[yelping]

00:16:15.533 --> 00:16:17.202
[wind howling]

00:16:17.286 --> 00:16:19.206
[straining]

00:16:19.290 --> 00:16:20.668
[CHIHO]
Please stop!

00:16:20.751 --> 00:16:23.298
Or at least tell me
why you're doing this!

00:16:23.381 --> 00:16:24.216
[LIBICOCCO]
Huh?

00:16:24.300 --> 00:16:25.761
I was given direct orders

00:16:25.845 --> 00:16:27.974
to go on the biggest rampage
I could muster

00:16:28.057 --> 00:16:29.728
wherever the Gate dropped me.

00:16:29.811 --> 00:16:31.732
Ah? But why, though?

00:16:31.815 --> 00:16:34.486
[chuckles]
It's a foolproof plan.

00:16:34.571 --> 00:16:38.996
You, the children inside,
everyone in this neighborhood.

00:16:39.079 --> 00:16:41.752
All those pouty cry-mouth faces.

00:16:41.835 --> 00:16:42.754
[gasps]

00:16:42.837 --> 00:16:44.507
It's quite
the delectable mission

00:16:44.591 --> 00:16:46.093
for a demon like me.

00:16:46.803 --> 00:16:48.431
The tears of the weak.

00:16:48.515 --> 00:16:50.268
Sorrow, and fear.

00:16:50.352 --> 00:16:52.774
All my favorite flavors!

00:16:52.857 --> 00:16:56.280
-Ah...
-[laughs]

00:16:57.491 --> 00:16:58.869
[gasps]

00:16:58.953 --> 00:17:00.623
[inhales sharply]
I can't breathe.

00:17:00.706 --> 00:17:03.127
It's like there's too much magic
in the air.

00:17:03.211 --> 00:17:06.133
-[CHIHO whimpers]
-Oh, how pathetic you are.

00:17:07.177 --> 00:17:08.931
-Huh?
-Uh?

00:17:09.724 --> 00:17:11.728
[scoffs]
If you have such a problem

00:17:11.812 --> 00:17:12.730
with what I'm doing,

00:17:12.814 --> 00:17:14.526
General Future Barista,

00:17:14.609 --> 00:17:18.116
I kindly invite you
to put an end to my antics.

00:17:18.199 --> 00:17:20.203
[SUZUNO]
Perfect. Then that I shall!

00:17:20.746 --> 00:17:22.667
-[thuds]
-[LIBICOCCO, CHIHO gasp]

00:17:22.750 --> 00:17:25.130
♪

00:17:25.213 --> 00:17:28.177
As a general, I'm sure
your offer extends to me.

00:17:28.261 --> 00:17:30.473
Though I might end more
than your antics.

00:17:30.558 --> 00:17:31.602
You made it!

00:17:31.685 --> 00:17:33.104
I'm sorry that I'm late.

00:17:34.023 --> 00:17:36.695
Breaking through the storm wall
was not a simple task.

00:17:36.778 --> 00:17:37.905
Quite a pain.

00:17:37.989 --> 00:17:38.991
-[URUSHIHARA] Hey!
-Ah!

00:17:39.074 --> 00:17:41.454
Don't let her think
you did it by yourself.

00:17:41.538 --> 00:17:44.001
I'm coming to her rescue
as much as you are, dude.

00:17:44.084 --> 00:17:46.255
Mister Urushihara, your wings!

00:17:46.339 --> 00:17:48.259
Hm? Oh. Clean, right?

00:17:48.343 --> 00:17:50.096
He drank some Holyvitan.

00:17:50.180 --> 00:17:52.309
Gotcha.
That explains the makeover.

00:17:52.894 --> 00:17:54.188
Looking back now,

00:17:54.271 --> 00:17:56.860
should've shot that magic juice
into my veins.

00:17:56.943 --> 00:17:58.488
Ya boy just wasn't ready.

00:17:58.572 --> 00:18:00.785
I suggest
you ready yourself now!

00:18:00.868 --> 00:18:02.454
[LIBICOCCO]
Lucifer, and...

00:18:02.538 --> 00:18:04.793
You must be Deathscythe Bel.

00:18:04.876 --> 00:18:05.711
Hm?

00:18:06.337 --> 00:18:08.383
Then you know
I was named a general?

00:18:08.466 --> 00:18:09.511
[LIBICOCCO]
Sorry.

00:18:09.594 --> 00:18:11.222
I hadn't the slightest suspicion

00:18:11.305 --> 00:18:13.519
that you all might make
an appearance.

00:18:14.854 --> 00:18:17.275
But thank you
for saving me the trip.

00:18:17.860 --> 00:18:18.695
[rain falling]

00:18:18.779 --> 00:18:19.781
[NORD] Miss Rika.

00:18:20.323 --> 00:18:23.037
I appreciate you.
For helping my Emilia.

00:18:23.121 --> 00:18:25.417
Oh. No problem at all.

00:18:25.500 --> 00:18:27.797
Hey, can you clear something up
for me?

00:18:27.880 --> 00:18:28.757
Of course.

00:18:28.841 --> 00:18:30.218
[RIKA]
Who's Emilia?

00:18:30.301 --> 00:18:32.431
Guess that's something else
you never knew.

00:18:32.515 --> 00:18:35.395
Emi Yusa's true name
is Emilia Justina.

00:18:35.478 --> 00:18:37.482
[RIKA]
And she's not from Japan either?

00:18:37.567 --> 00:18:39.194
Well, uh... [clears throat]

00:18:41.282 --> 00:18:42.159
Uh...

00:18:42.785 --> 00:18:43.620
She's not.

00:18:44.204 --> 00:18:45.791
It sounds absurd,

00:18:45.875 --> 00:18:47.712
but she wasn't even born
on Earth.

00:18:49.047 --> 00:18:50.175
Emi's an alien?

00:18:50.843 --> 00:18:52.012
[ASHIYA]
That's a rather simple way

00:18:52.095 --> 00:18:52.930
to look at it,

00:18:53.014 --> 00:18:54.642
but I think you get the point.

00:18:54.726 --> 00:18:56.187
She's like an alien.

00:18:56.688 --> 00:18:58.901
But she's human
through and through.

00:18:58.984 --> 00:19:00.236
No doubt about that.

00:19:00.320 --> 00:19:02.742
Just, one from a faraway world.

00:19:04.453 --> 00:19:05.748
Do you think I'm stupid?

00:19:06.457 --> 00:19:09.087
Of course not,
but you have to believe me.

00:19:09.171 --> 00:19:10.173
Otherwise,

00:19:10.256 --> 00:19:12.302
you'll never understand
what you've seen.

00:19:12.385 --> 00:19:14.766
Because it's honestly
the truth of the matter.

00:19:14.849 --> 00:19:16.728
[RIKA]
What are you talking about?

00:19:17.855 --> 00:19:19.483
[ASHIYA]
That house over there.

00:19:19.567 --> 00:19:22.030
It's a good ten meters away,
wouldn't you say?

00:19:22.113 --> 00:19:24.409
Can you imagine
any ordinary person

00:19:24.493 --> 00:19:26.288
just hopping over to the roof?

00:19:26.372 --> 00:19:27.290
Ah!

00:19:27.374 --> 00:19:29.002
Well, I mean, uh...

00:19:29.086 --> 00:19:30.255
It is pretty far.

00:19:30.338 --> 00:19:31.508
But you're kidding!

00:19:31.591 --> 00:19:33.929
Though I can understand
your disbelief.

00:19:34.012 --> 00:19:35.516
I'm quite serious.

00:19:35.599 --> 00:19:37.310
-Then show me some proof!
-[slams]

00:19:37.394 --> 00:19:38.564
You know,
none of what you're saying

00:19:38.647 --> 00:19:40.191
makes any kind of sense.

00:19:40.275 --> 00:19:43.281
Why would an alien be working
for peanuts at a call center?

00:19:43.364 --> 00:19:45.578
I've asked myself
the same question.

00:19:45.661 --> 00:19:48.499
But still, we all have to eat
and pay the rent.

00:19:48.584 --> 00:19:50.546
And that requires keeping a job.

00:19:51.213 --> 00:19:56.223
[speaking in foreign language]

00:20:03.154 --> 00:20:04.489
What all do you know?

00:20:04.574 --> 00:20:06.452
Did Maou explain who we are?

00:20:06.536 --> 00:20:07.454
Not yet.

00:20:08.331 --> 00:20:09.834
But I'm starting
to get the feeling

00:20:09.918 --> 00:20:11.546
that none of you are human.

00:20:11.630 --> 00:20:13.049
As for now...

00:20:13.132 --> 00:20:13.967
[grunts]

00:20:14.051 --> 00:20:15.888
I'll have to wait
to get a real introduction

00:20:15.971 --> 00:20:16.806
and all that.

00:20:16.890 --> 00:20:18.309
[gasps and grunts]

00:20:18.392 --> 00:20:20.814
[rain falling]

00:20:20.898 --> 00:20:25.824
♪

00:20:25.908 --> 00:20:27.452
It looks like we're surrounded.

00:20:28.204 --> 00:20:29.414
Where's that armor from?

00:20:29.916 --> 00:20:31.251
Never seen it before.

00:20:31.836 --> 00:20:33.089
The Eastern Continent.

00:20:33.799 --> 00:20:37.389
The second-highest ranking
of Efzahan's knight squadrons,

00:20:37.472 --> 00:20:39.184
the Inlaid Azure Scarves.

00:20:39.686 --> 00:20:40.688
But why?

00:20:40.771 --> 00:20:42.107
What have they come for?

00:20:42.190 --> 00:20:44.862
I got some of that,
but I'm completely lost.

00:20:44.946 --> 00:20:48.494
We need to protect her,
Miss Rika, don't we?

00:20:49.079 --> 00:20:49.914
Correct.

00:20:50.582 --> 00:20:51.417
Ah!

00:20:52.085 --> 00:20:53.421
And you're a fighter?

00:20:53.922 --> 00:20:54.966
Well, sometimes.

00:20:55.049 --> 00:20:58.264
I could take on this large
of a squadron back at home,

00:20:58.347 --> 00:20:59.349
but here...

00:20:59.433 --> 00:21:02.272
I've had my fair share of fights
from time to time.

00:21:02.773 --> 00:21:03.859
But I'm untrained.

00:21:04.652 --> 00:21:06.321
Are they looking for me?

00:21:06.405 --> 00:21:07.365
No, doubt it.

00:21:08.242 --> 00:21:10.789
The only reason I'm here
is because I met Maou.

00:21:11.833 --> 00:21:13.252
He's their target.

00:21:13.335 --> 00:21:14.881
That's probably the case.

00:21:14.964 --> 00:21:16.760
-[whimpers]
-[sighs]

00:21:16.843 --> 00:21:18.638
[ASHIYA] If we assume
that whatever happened

00:21:18.722 --> 00:21:19.891
at Miss Sasaki's school

00:21:19.974 --> 00:21:21.561
was simply a diversion,

00:21:21.644 --> 00:21:22.813
then it follows they've come

00:21:22.897 --> 00:21:25.944
to collect the most likely one
to stay behind in a crisis.

00:21:27.030 --> 00:21:28.365
Furthermore,

00:21:28.449 --> 00:21:30.662
if one of us can't fight
at the moment...

00:21:31.371 --> 00:21:33.083
that narrows it down to...

00:21:33.877 --> 00:21:34.837
[grunts]

00:21:35.798 --> 00:21:37.008
...me.

00:21:37.091 --> 00:21:39.221
I'm the one that they're after.

00:21:39.304 --> 00:21:43.730
-[rain falling]
-[train engine chugging]

00:21:43.814 --> 00:21:46.235
[door sliding]

00:21:46.318 --> 00:21:48.239
[AMANE]
Ugh. Stupid rain.

00:21:48.782 --> 00:21:50.159
Should I take a cab?

00:21:50.243 --> 00:21:51.078
It's not far,

00:21:51.161 --> 00:21:53.040
so probably more trouble
than it's worth.

00:21:53.834 --> 00:21:55.921
Not like I'm gonna melt
or anything.

00:21:56.004 --> 00:21:57.340
-[wind whooshing]
-[gasps]

00:21:57.423 --> 00:21:59.512
Mm? What in the--

00:21:59.595 --> 00:22:00.639
[sniffing]

00:22:01.599 --> 00:22:04.479
Yeah. Too funky for a cab.

00:22:04.564 --> 00:22:08.028
Ugh. I'd literally kill
for a bath right about now.

00:22:08.112 --> 00:22:09.030
Okay.

00:22:09.657 --> 00:22:10.491
Now!

00:22:11.118 --> 00:22:16.128
[yelping]

